HEADWORD: Gloriation
<hw>Glo`ri*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>gloriatio</ets>, from <ets>gloriari</ets> to glory, boast, fr.
<ets>gloria</ets> glory. See <er>Glory</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety>
<def>Boast; a triumphing.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Bp.
Richardson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Internal <qex>gloriation</qex> or triumph of the mind.</q>
